korean:
  title: 구잠
  author: 이제현
  language: kor
  text: 꼬리로는 아첨을 부리고 혀[舌]로는 핥아 빤다. 싸우거나 장난치지 말라, 울타리 망가진다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0520_030_0060&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Admonition to the Dog
  author: Lee Jehyeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    With tail you flatter and fawn,
    With tongue you lick and grovel.
    Do not quarrel, do not play—
    The fence lies broken in your wake.
  footnotes:
    - The poem uses the dog as a vehicle for satire, likely critiquing human behavior and social vices rather than addressing canine conduct literally.
